race.comment: MADRINA (4) started favourite and did work home in fine style but found one better last start over 1000m at this track. Unplaced twice over this distance last prep but they were in far stronger races in Melbourne. This looks an ideal set up at this stage of the prep. CAESAR (7) was lining up for only the second time, and was fresh from a three-month break, when beaten under a length over 1100m at Hawkesbury last time out. Raced three-wide with no cover that day to add to the merit of the performance. Hard to stop over the extra 100m. I AM BRAVE (10) was well backed but never really got involved from back in the field when resuming over this trip at Newcastle last start. Promising mare who needs luck from a wide gate but can feature in the finish. VIIPURI (15) ticks plenty of boxes today following an impressive debut win at Orange. Tougher here but he looks up to the mark and can remain unbeaten.
